{
  "texts": [
    "Most commonly, these features are used in a simple pipeline of transformation followed by a classifier (see Fig. 8).",
    "Several toolkits exist for extracting features.",
    "The flowchart in Fig. 9 displays the feature based algorithms described in this section and related algorithms.",
    "The highly comparative time-series analysis (hctsa) (Fulcher and Jones 2017) toolbox can create over 7700 features for exploratory time series analysis.",
    "The canonical time series characteristics (Catch22) (Lubba et al. 2019) are 22 hctsa features determined to be the most discriminatory of the full set."
  ]
}